{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Regarding the problem of scalability, the choice of consensus algorithms affects significantly the throughput, for example, using the Proof Of Stake consensus algorithm which provides superior performance than Proof of Work (PoW) consensus algorithm has been proposed [29].",
    "In this regard, we note that the Ethereum blockchain officially switched to Proof of Stake (PoS) consensus mechanism, which makes it more suitable for building distributed applications [65].",
    "Whereas Mulyati et al. [32] and Ma [35] used Delegated Proof of Stake (DPOS) algorithm which is more efficient in performance and energy [32].",
    "Meanwhile, the authors in [51] proposed reputation-based delegated proof of stake (RDPoS) consensus algorithm which demonstrated high transaction throughput.",
    "Another design decision is to use permissioned blockchains (HyperLedger Fabric) which offer higher throughput than public blockchain solutions [7]."
  ],
